she has pawned the jewelry, farmlands,

287
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:03,320
and shops that you owned.

288
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:06,160
I rushed to buy back a few of them.

289
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:08,840
But for the farmlands and shops,

290
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:11,040
the prices being asked were too expensive.

291
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:12,160
I was unable to buy them back.

292
00:19:12,840 --> 00:19:14,680
Once you've driven her away,

293
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:15,920
you can just buy them back yourself.

294
00:19:21,840 --> 00:19:22,840
This is impossible.

295
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:26,960
Young Master, look.

296
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:30,920
I've followed her for more than ten days.

297
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:33,040
She will hide the items

298
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:34,880
in a concealed part

299
00:19:34,880 --> 00:19:36,360
of the kitchen every night.

300
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:37,796
And then in the morning,

301
00:19:37,796 --> 00:19:38,840
when she buys ingredients from the market,

302
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:40,800
she will hand it to a man.

303
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:43,280
I wanted to tell it to you when I discovered it.

304
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:45,560
But you were sick then

305
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:46,720
so I was afraid you wouldn't be able to take it.

306
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:49,240
I could only hide

307
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:50,240
those valuable ones first,

308
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:52,160
but the house is only that big!

309
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:53,240
How long can I hide them?

310
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:55,560
She was able to find most of them.

311
00:19:56,960 --> 00:19:58,760
Now you're better,

312
00:19:58,760 --> 00:19:59,640
but not many valuables

313
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:01,920
are left in our house!

314
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:15,840
Impossible...

315
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:19,120
Impossible...

316
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:20,000
Young Master Ye!

317
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:21,237
Could it be that our servants stole them from us

318
00:20:21,237 --> 00:20:21,840
and sold them outside?

319
00:20:21,840 --> 00:20:22,800
I personally saw her enter the pawnshop!

320
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:26,320
Young Master Ye!

321
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:28,000
Has your heart been blinded by pig oil?

322
00:20:28,320 --> 00:20:29,840
She's not a good person!

323
00:20:34,530 --> 00:20:35,480
Young Master Ye!

324
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:37,320
Nanny...

325
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:39,600
While a person is alive,

326
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:40,920
no matter how huge a problem is,

327
00:20:41,070 --> 00:20:42,600
avoiding it is useless.

328
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:44,680
I know.

329
00:20:45,470 --> 00:20:46,880
I know that you

330
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:47,960
treat her as your heart's solace,

331
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:48,960
hence you're refusing to admit it.

332
00:20:50,090 --> 00:20:51,440
But are you willing

333
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:54,278
to be played with by others in the palm

334
00:20:54,278 --> 00:20:54,920
of their hands?

335
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:57,920
To say something that's overstepping my boundary,

336
00:20:59,480 --> 00:20:59,960
I've treated you

337
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:01,600
like my own child.

338
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:03,840
I know that in your heart,

339
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:05,240
you have

340
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:07,240
a place for me.

341
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,160
I won't beg you

342
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,440
to trust me now,

343
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:13,960
I only beg you to personally follow

344
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:15,080
that woman tomorrow!

345
00:21:16,260 --> 00:21:17,200
If she obediently comes home

346
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:18,320
upon buying some food,

347
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:22,440
I will never mention this matter again!

348
00:22:03,760 --> 00:22:04,560
Young Master.

349
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:06,960
Young Master, look.

350
00:22:08,320 --> 00:22:09,520
He's actually alive.

351
00:22:29,720 --> 00:22:30,560
Darling Second, you are back.

352
00:22:35,560 --> 00:22:37,242
You have been out for the whole day.

353
00:22:37,242 --> 00:22:37,922
You must be tired.

354
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:44,320
Come.

355
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:48,640
The meal has already been cooked.

356
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,520
I will get it for you later.

357
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:55,040
What's wrong?

358
00:22:56,240 --> 00:22:58,280
Manniang,

359
00:22:58,280 --> 00:22:59,640
I have something to ask you.

360
00:23:02,560 --> 00:23:04,560
What is it? Once we get done eating,

361
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:06,120
you can ask me again later.

362
00:23:08,880 --> 00:23:09,840
I'm asking now.

363
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:14,960
Okay, fine.

364
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:18,000
Darling Second, just ask if you have anything to ask.

365
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:19,920
I'm listening.

366
00:23:27,080 --> 00:23:28,760
I promised Nanny Chang that

367
00:23:28,760 --> 00:23:30,360
I would give her a coffin.

368
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:34,000
Now I'm poor and frustrated,

369
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:37,040
but I can't break my promise to her.

370
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:40,360
I was thinking,

371
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:41,840
we still have some money

372
00:23:42,840 --> 00:23:43,960
and can make some preparations in advance for her.

373
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:46,720
I found a carpenter

374
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:49,840
and gave him five taels in silver as deposit.

375
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:53,880
As for the balance, I will gradually pay it.

376
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,160
It's just that,

377
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:00,600
I'm a bit tight with money now.

378
00:24:02,120 --> 00:24:03,040
I was thinking.

379
00:24:03,840 --> 00:24:04,800
I gave the children

380
00:24:04,800 --> 00:24:06,360
two gold locks.

381
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:09,280
Go to look for them and bring them to me now.

382
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:12,040
I...

383
00:24:14,360 --> 00:24:16,240
I don't know where they are.

384
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:19,720
I will look for them tomorrow and give them to you.

385
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:24,960
I will look for the money now.

386
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:32,000
It's dark now, and I can't see clearly.

387
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:34,560
I don't know where I put them.

388
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:39,880
Light the candle then.

389
00:24:41,160 --> 00:24:42,800
Light every single

390
00:24:42,800 --> 00:24:43,760
candle in the house.

391
00:24:57,560 --> 00:24:59,920
Darling Second...

392
00:24:59,920 --> 00:25:03,040
those golden locks...

393
00:25:03,960 --> 00:25:05,760
I sold them.

394
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:11,040
Nanny Chang told me that

395
00:25:11,040 --> 00:25:12,640
we will be having a hard time in the future.

396
00:25:14,080 --> 00:25:15,400
I've given it a lot of thought,

397
00:25:16,560 --> 00:25:17,435
and decided to sell the jewelry

398
00:25:17,435 --> 00:25:18,040
and antiques for money,

399
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:20,320
rather than just leaving them here

400
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:21,840
in the house for display.

401
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:24,600
Running some small business

402
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:25,520
is also a way to make a living.

403
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:28,800
It's not important that we have a hard time.

404
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:30,520
What's important is that we can still

405
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:31,960
support our children.

406
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:40,560
Why did you hide this from me?

407
00:25:43,430 --> 00:25:44,720
We have been rich before.

408
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:47,280
Now we have to live our days

409
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:49,200
by pawning valuables.

410
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:52,160
I was afraid that you wouldn't be able to take it.

411
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:53,320
That's why I hid it from you.

412
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:56,440
The Old Marquis just passed away.

413
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:58,720
Look at the way the Gu family treats you.

414
00:25:58,720 --> 00:26:00,120
There are many matters pressing on us.

415
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:05,760
Since young,

416
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:07,680
I have been growing up in poverty and hardship.

417
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,760
I don't care about pawning anything.

418
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:13,920
But Darling Second,

419
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:15,720
you grew up with a silver spoon.

420
00:26:16,570 --> 00:26:18,040
I was afraid you wouldn't be able to take it.

421
00:26:19,360 --> 00:26:21,280
That's why

422
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:22,800
I thought of selling them first

423
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:25,280
and then tell you about it later.

424
00:26:34,360 --> 00:26:35,440
Darling Second,

425
00:26:37,040 --> 00:26:38,680
if you think that I tricked you,

426
00:26:39,600 --> 00:26:40,240
you...

427
00:26:42,140 --> 00:26:43,840
Just kill me with a sword!

428
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:46,000
I have been sincere

429
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,320
and serving you for many years.

430
00:26:48,320 --> 00:26:49,520
If you kill me,

431
00:26:49,520 --> 00:26:50,600
I won't blame you either!

432
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:54,200
It's just that,

433
00:26:54,200 --> 00:26:56,200
before I die,

434
00:26:57,280 --> 00:26:58,480
let me see

435
00:26:58,480 --> 00:26:59,720
my children first.

436
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:03,560
These two children are very pitiful.

437
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:06,880
As long as you can raise them

438
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:08,280
well in the future,

439
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:12,280
I will die without any regrets.

440
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:15,040
Darling Second!

441
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:25,920
Stop being foolish.

442
00:27:29,120 --> 00:27:30,600
This is Dongjing,

443
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:31,680
under the feet of the Emperor.

444
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:33,440
How can anyone be killed at random?

445
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:35,880
You only sold some gold

446
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:38,360
and silver jewelry.

447
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:40,920
How can this be an offense requiring a death?

448
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:44,400
Darling Second.

449
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:47,040
Don't blame me, okay?

450
00:27:52,440 --> 00:27:54,080
What else did you hide from me?

451
00:27:58,080 --> 00:27:59,040
Nothing else.

452
00:28:01,080 --> 00:28:02,000
There's nothing else.

453
00:28:24,880 --> 00:28:26,760
You are illiterate.

454
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:27,800
I will read it to you.

455
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:32,920
"Almost thirty hectare of fertile land

456
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:35,760
in the Dongsan Village of Guojia Farm,

457
00:28:36,040 --> 00:28:37,600
western outskirts of Bianjing."

458
00:28:41,880 --> 00:28:45,385
"Southern side of the Niu Farm in the eastern

459
00:28:45,385 --> 00:28:47,800
outskirts of Rongde in Sichuan...

460
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,440
over twenty hectare of dry land."

461
00:28:51,240 --> 00:28:53,800
This...what is this?

462
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:58,280
"Thirty salt shops on Yangzhou Road."

463
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:08,440
Manniang,

464
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:09,760
I'm asking you one more time.

465
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:12,960
What else did you hide from me?

466
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:16,680
As long as you tell me,

467
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:17,920
I will let bygones be bygones.

468
00:29:30,170 --> 00:29:30,986
You are still asking me

469
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:32,280
what else I have hidden from you?

470
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:34,400
I would like to ask you, Darling Second,

471
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:36,600
why did you trick me instead?

472
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:40,080
When did I trick you?

473
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:43,720
You are very cruel!

474
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:46,280
You caused me to think that

475
00:29:46,280 --> 00:29:47,920
we are running out of rice soon.

476
00:29:48,240 --> 00:29:49,560
I didn't even want my dignity!

477
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:51,175
I went out to pawn things

478
00:29:51,175 --> 00:29:52,200
so we could get on with our days.

479
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:53,480
How many supercilious looks must I endure?

480
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:55,280
Who knew that

481
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:58,440
you would hide your personal assets that well?

482
00:30:00,240 --> 00:30:01,247
You said you did this for

483
00:30:01,247 --> 00:30:02,440
our children's sake and my own.

484
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:04,360
Why did you trick me?

485
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:09,120
So you're saying I should be apologetic

486
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:10,680
toward you instead?

487
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:25,640
What are you doing? Oh my God.

488
00:30:26,440 --> 00:30:27,280
Look.

489
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:30,360
The pawnshop at Yongle street

490
00:30:30,360 --> 00:30:31,640
in Suzhou deed,

491
00:30:33,720 --> 00:30:34,960
you burned it!

492
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:40,040
This one asset could have supported us

493
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:41,320
for a lifetime!

494
00:30:43,540 --> 00:30:45,360
Didn't you say you were illiterate?

495
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:47,920
How did you manage to understand

496
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:49,400
every single word on this deed?

497
00:30:51,760 --> 00:30:54,000
Manniang,

498
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:55,560
I'm asking you the last time.

499
00:30:57,840 --> 00:30:59,640
What else did you hide from me?

500
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:17,520
N-Nothing. Nothing else.

501
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:19,400
Bring him in!

502
00:31:33,440 --> 00:31:34,120
Brother?

503
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:39,400
You said that your older brother tricked you

504
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:40,960
out of your savings

505
00:31:42,240 --> 00:31:43,600
and later died on the way.

506
00:31:44,880 --> 00:31:46,680
You had no one to rely on and took shelter with me.

507
00:31:48,230 --> 00:31:50,000
I gave you money for shelter

508
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:51,160
and bought a grave for you,

509
00:31:51,880 --> 00:31:54,120
and personally witnessed your older brother's coffin

510
00:31:54,120 --> 00:31:54,880
being lowered in the ground!

511
00:31:57,920 --> 00:32:00,240
I'm asking you now.

512
00:32:00,240 --> 00:32:01,480
What else are you hiding from me?

513
00:32:03,320 --> 00:32:05,680
Isn't this the biggest joke?

514
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,760
Darling Second, Darling Second!

515
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:13,640
I was tricked

516
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,320
by my older brother.

517
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:17,640
I was tricked by him!

518
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:20,240
Darling Second...

519
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:22,760
Manniang,

520
00:32:22,760 --> 00:32:23,760
if you didn't see

521
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:26,520
that I was wealthy now,

522
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:27,480
I fear you and your older brother

523
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:28,880
would have run away with the shop.

524
00:32:30,680 --> 00:32:32,120
Thanks to me for always speaking up

525
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:33,400
on your behalf in front of my nanny,

526
00:32:35,530 --> 00:32:37,000
and insisting that I didn't misjudge you.

527
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:38,640
Darling Second!

528
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:43,080
Darling Second...

529
00:32:52,240 --> 00:32:54,360
Take your so-called deceased older brother,

530
00:32:55,960 --> 00:32:58,680
and get lost

531
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:00,160
tomorrow morning.

532
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:03,760
Darling Second?

533
00:33:05,320 --> 00:33:07,640
Darling Second! Darling Second!

534
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:26,520
Get in there!

535
00:33:48,480 --> 00:33:49,480
Darling Second...

536
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:54,840
For the sake of the children,

537
00:33:56,690 --> 00:33:58,400
forgive me this time.

538
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:01,600
Let me stay in the house.

539
00:34:09,920 --> 00:34:10,920
Darling Second...

540
00:34:15,440 --> 00:34:17,280
I don't want any title.

541
00:34:19,160 --> 00:34:21,200
I'm fine not being an outside mistress either.

542
00:34:22,600 --> 00:34:23,440
Just treat me...

543
00:34:24,880 --> 00:34:26,240
as an additional female attendant

544
00:34:26,240 --> 00:34:27,480
in the house.

545
00:34:29,760 --> 00:34:30,880
The two children can't

546
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:33,160
lose their biological mother.

547
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:44,280
Darling Second, you are a kind person.

548
00:34:45,600 --> 00:34:48,960
You gave me those funds,

549
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:53,000
but my hateful older brother

550
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:55,200
lost them all

551
00:34:55,200 --> 00:34:56,360
in gambling.

552
00:34:58,120 --> 00:34:59,880
He asked me to repeatedly fool you

553
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:02,480
to get him those items.

554
00:35:04,200 --> 00:35:06,280
I was just forced to do it.

555
00:35:07,720 --> 00:35:09,760
He said...

556
00:35:09,760 --> 00:35:11,680
that if I didn't give him that money,

557
00:35:12,800 --> 00:35:14,320
he would abduct the two children.

558
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:17,680
He would kidnap them!

559
00:35:19,920 --> 00:35:21,840
Darling Second,

560
00:35:21,840 --> 00:35:24,120
I don't have any skills.

561
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:26,333
If I wander around,

562
00:35:26,333 --> 00:35:27,840
I won't have any family to rely on.

563
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:32,760
I really have no choice left!

564
00:35:39,560 --> 00:35:41,160
If I were still penniless now,

565
00:35:43,120 --> 00:35:44,880
would you still cry and shout like that

566
00:35:44,880 --> 00:35:45,640
so that you can stay?

567
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:48,000
I would.

568
00:35:50,680 --> 00:35:51,760
I would.

569
00:35:56,200 --> 00:35:57,120
Darling Second

570
00:35:58,840 --> 00:36:01,400
Since you were little, you haven't had a mother

571
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:02,920
to take care of you.

572
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:05,200
You know the hardship of two children not

573
